<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="will-modal-v">will <strong><em>modal v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /wɪl/    美 /wɪl/  </p>
<p>(would)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[表示单纯的将来] 将要；会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We will catch the 3:30 train. 
我们要赶3点30分的火车。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[表示意志、意愿、建议、决心等] 愿；要；定要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I will do my best to help you. 
我会尽力帮你。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Will you type this, please? 
你是否可以把这个打出来呢?</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[表示功能] 能；行：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This will do if there is nothing better. 
如果没有更好的，这个也行。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>[表示推测] 可能；大概：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That will be the postman at the door, I suppose. 
我想门外可能是邮递员。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>[表示习惯、经常性、倾向性等] 惯于；总是：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’ll listen to music, alone in her room, for hours. 
她总是独自一个人在房间听音乐，一听就是几个小时。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The door <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ open, no matter how hard she pushed.  （2013 全国）<br />
A.shouldn’t<br />
B.couldn’t<br />
C.wouldn’t<br />
D.mightn’t  </li>
<li>— Goodbye, John. Come back again sometime.
— Sure. I <strong><em>_</em></strong>_.   （2012 四川改）<br />
A.I did<br />
B.I do<br />
C.I shall  </li>
<li>— Mr Gordon asked me to remind you of the meeting this afternoon. Don’t you forget it!
— OK, I <strong><em>_</em></strong>_.  （2006 重庆改）<br />
B.don’t<br />
C.will<br />
D.do  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. C  2. will  3. won’t  </p></div>